  "texts": [
    "Step III: Evaluation of QualityThe main goal of quality evaluation is to examine the selected research articles that are pertinent to the work-study and i.e., used to address our research issue.",
    "Conceptual relevance, mathematical modeling and correlation of methods used to address NER issues are some of the quality factors.These state-of-the-art summaries are made in accordance with these criteria for excellence and they guarantee the clear presentation of the state-of-the-art by utilizing tables related to various sub-strings.",
    "Regarding the contribution of the primary article chosen, the table itself is self-explanatory.",
    "It also includes suggestions for improvement/demerits that might be made with regard to 110 research papers.",
    "One manual, three reports and 75 additional publications that were different from the keywords and, due to being read, complete knowledge incorporated into the collection are included in this research article."
  ]
}